# NEVER UTF-16 — ALWAYS UTF-8 NO BOM (ABSOLUTE)

> **ABSOLUTE**: **NEVER use UTF-16** (LE or BE). **ALWAYS use UTF-8 without BOM** for every text file you create or edit. No exceptions.

UTF-16 on Windows (especially from the Cursor Write/StrReplace tools) corrupts source files with null-padded ASCII and breaks compilers. This rule is non-negotiable.

**Every file you create or edit MUST be saved as UTF-8 without BOM.** Applies to all text: HTML, Rust, TypeScript, CSS, JSON, Markdown, rules, skills, configs, scripts, SQL, and docs.

Forbidden encodings: **UTF-16 (LE/BE)** — never, UTF-8 with BOM, Windows-1252, Latin-1, or any other legacy encoding.

## Required on write

1. **Encoding** — UTF-8, no BOM. First bytes must NOT be `EF BB BF` (BOM) or `FF FE` / `FE FF` (UTF-16).
2. **HTML** — every HTML document must include `<meta charset="UTF-8">` in `<head>`.
3. **HTTP headers** — text responses must use `Content-Type: ...; charset=utf-8`.
4. **Rust** — use UTF-8 string literals for non-ASCII text; no raw bytes or `\xNN` escapes for readable text.
5. **PowerShell** — NEVER use `Set-Content -Encoding UTF8` on Windows PowerShell 5.1 (adds BOM). Use:
   ```powershell
   $utf8 = New-Object System.Text.UTF8Encoding $false
   [System.IO.File]::WriteAllText($path, $content, $utf8)
   ```
   PowerShell 7+: `-Encoding utf8NoBOM`.
6. **Cursor Write/StrReplace on Windows** — may produce UTF-16. After every write, verify first bytes are NOT null-padded ASCII. Re-save via `[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText` with `UTF8Encoding($false)` if needed.

## Pre-write check

- Encoding is explicitly UTF-8 without BOM (not UTF-16).
- Does the file contain non-ASCII (accents, emoji, symbols)?
- Are HTML/HTTP charset declarations present?

## Post-write check (mandatory for text/HTML/code)

1. **Read the file back** — confirm non-ASCII renders correctly (no `Ã©`, `â€™`, `Ã«`, `ï»¿`, U+FFFD replacement character).
2. **Scan for mojibake patterns** — `Ã`, `Â`, `â€`, `ï»¿`, replacement character.
3. **Verify bytes** — no BOM prefix, no UTF-16 null bytes between ASCII characters (`FF FE`, `FE FF`, or `H e l l o` with nulls).
4. **Fix immediately** if wrong — rewrite as UTF-8 without BOM.

Do not finish a write without this check when the file is text/HTML/code.

## Examples

```html
<!-- GOOD -->
<head><meta charset="UTF-8"><title>ax</title></head>

<!-- BAD - missing charset -->
<head><title>ax</title></head>
```

```rust
// GOOD
"Content-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8"

// BAD
"Content-Type: text/html"
```

```powershell
# GOOD - UTF-8 no BOM
$utf8 = New-Object System.Text.UTF8Encoding $false
[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText($path, $content, $utf8)

# BAD - UTF-16 or BOM
Set-Content -Path $path -Value $content -Encoding UTF8
Set-Content -Path $path -Value $content -Encoding Unicode
```

Project default: see `.editorconfig` (`charset = utf-8`).